sorders. The comorbidity between disorders was mainly (63\%) due to additive genetic effects common to both disorders. Interpretation: Similar to molecular genetic studies, we showed evidence that schizophrenia and bipolar disorder partly share a common genetic cause. These results challenge the current nosological dichotomy between schizophrenia and bipolar disorder, and are consistent with a reappraisal of these disorders as distinct diagnostic entities. Funding: Swedish Council for Working Life and Social Research, and the Swedish Research Council. © 2009 Elsevier Ltd. All rights reserved.},
